  "text": "## HTTP Request Header Injection Validation in Envoy v1.31.2\n\nEnvoy implements comprehensive HTTP request header injection validation and prevention through multiple layers of defense across three main HTTP protocol implementations (HTTP/1.1, HTTP/2, HTTP/3).\n\n### Core Header Validation Functions\n\n**Basic Header Validation (source/common/http/header_utility.cc)**\n- `validHeaderString()` (envoy/http/header_map.h): Validates header strings do not contain embedded NULLs, carriage returns (\\r), or line feeds (\\n)\n- `headerNameIsValid()`: Validates header names according to HTTP semantics, checks for valid characters, handles pseudo-headers starting with ':'\n- `headerValueIsValid()`: Validates header values using http2::adapter::HeaderValidator for RFC compliance\n- `checkValidRequestHeaders()`: Comprehensive validation of upstream request headers (guarded by \"envoy.reloadable_features.validate_upstream_headers\" runtime flag)\n- `checkRequiredRequestHeaders()`: Ensures required headers (:method, :path, :authority for CONNECT) are present\n- `requestHeadersValid()`: Validates authority, method, and scheme headers for compliance\n\n### Internal Header Stripping and Forbidden Headers\n\n**Edge Request Header Sanitization (source/common/http/conn_manager_utility.cc)**\n- `cleanInternalHeaders()`: Removes internal x-envoy-* headers from edge requests to prevent clients from injecting values that should only come from trusted internal sources. Headers stripped include:\n  - x-envoy-decorator-operation\n  - x-envoy-downstream-service-cluster  \n  - x-envoy-downstream-service-node\n  - x-envoy-original-path\n  - x-envoy-retry-on / x-envoy-retry-grpc-on\n  - x-envoy-max-retries\n  - x-envoy-upstream-alt-stat-name\n  - x-envoy-upstream-request-timeout-ms / x-envoy-upstream-request-per-try-timeout-ms\n  - x-envoy-force-trace\n  - x-envoy-ip-tags\n  - x-envoy-original-url\n  - x-envoy-hedge-on-per-try-timeout\n\n### Connection Header Sanitization\n\n**HTTP/1.1 Connection Header Handling (source/common/http/utility.cc)**\n- `sanitizeConnectionHeader()`: Prevents header injection via the Connection header by:\n  - Limiting nominated headers to 10 maximum (prevents DOS)\n  - Removing headers nominated by the Connection header\n  - Rejecting if Connection nominates x-forwarded-* headers or pseudo-headers (RFC violation)\n  - Sanitizing the TE (Transfer-Encoding) header when nominated\n  - Validating TE values do not exceed 256 bytes\n  - Validates nominated headers conform to HTTP hop-by-hop semantics\n\n### HTTP/1.1 Specific Validation\n\n**Header Codec Validation (source/common/http/http1/codec_impl.cc)**\n- Validates header values for invalid characters using `headerValueIsValid()`\n- Checks header names and values conform to HTTP/1.1 semantics\n- Validates path formatting and rejects invalid URLs\n- Calls `sanitizeConnectionHeader()` during request header processing\n- Detects invalid header values (non-ASCII, control characters)\n\n**HTTP/1 Header Validator (source/extensions/http/header_validators/envoy_default/http1_header_validator.cc)**\n- `sanitizeContentLength()`: Removes content-length from CONNECT requests or when transfer-encoding:chunked is present\n- `sanitizeHeadersWithUnderscores()`: Removes or rejects headers with underscores based on configuration\n- `sanitizePathWithFragment()`: Strips URL fragments from paths\n- `transformRequestHeaders()`: Applies all sanitization transformations in sequence\n- Validates header character sets conform to RFC specifications\n- Supports path normalization with escaped slash handling\n\n### HTTP/2 Specific Validation  \n\n**HTTP/2 Forbidden Headers (source/extensions/http/header_validators/envoy_default/http2_header_validator.cc)**\n- Enforces strict validation that connection-specific headers are forbidden in HTTP/2 per RFC 9113\n- Forbidden header list: transfer-encoding, connection, upgrade, keep-alive, proxy-connection\n- Returns ConnectionHeaderSanitization rejection code (uhv.http2.connection_header_rejected) when these headers are detected\n- Validates header names are lowercase (HTTP/2 requirement)\n- Rejects headers with uppercase letters (HTTP/2 compliance)\n- Rejects header names with underscores if configured (headers_with_underscores_action)\n- Validates empty header names are rejected\n\n### Path and Query Validation\n\n**Path Validation (source/extensions/http/header_validators/envoy_default/header_validator.cc)**\n- `validatePathHeaderCharacters()`: Validates path contains only RFC 3986 compliant characters\n- `sanitizeEncodedSlashes()`: Handles percent-encoded slashes (%2F, %5C) with configurable behavior\n- `sanitizePathWithFragment()`: Removes URL fragments from paths\n- `transformUrlPath()`: Normalizes paths and validates encoded sequences\n- Supports disabling path normalization while still validating character sets\n- Detects and prevents null byte injection (%00) in paths\n- Supports configurable character sets for path compliance modes\n\n### HTTP/3 (QUIC) Header Validation\n\n**QUIC Stream Validation (source/common/quic/envoy_quic_stream.h, source/common/quic/envoy_quic_server_stream.cc)**\n- `validateHeader()`: Per-header validation for QUIC streams using http2::adapter::HeaderValidator\n- Validates content-length headers for QUIC protocol requirements\n- Supports stream-specific error handling for invalid headers\n- Configuration option: override_stream_error_on_invalid_http_message\n- Validates header names and values against HTTP/2 semantics (QUIC uses HTTP/2 header encoding)\n\n**QUIC Utilities (source/common/quic/envoy_quic_utils.h)**\n- `quicHeadersToEnvoyHeaders()`: Converts QUIC headers to Envoy format with validation\n- Enforces max header count and size limits during conversion\n- Supports header validator interface for custom validation\n\n### Header Underscore Handling\n\n**Underscore Sanitization (source/extensions/http/header_validators/envoy_default/header_validator.cc)**\n- `sanitizeHeadersWithUnderscores()`: Drops or rejects headers containing underscores\n- Configurable via HeaderValidatorConfig.headers_with_underscores_action:\n  - ALLOW: Permits underscores\n  - DROP_HEADER: Silently removes headers with underscores\n  - REJECT_REQUEST: Returns validation error\n- Stats tracking for dropped headers\n\n### Runtime Configuration and Guards\n\nKey runtime guards controlling header validation behavior:\n- `envoy.reloadable_features.validate_upstream_headers`: Enables validation of upstream request headers\n- `envoy.reloadable_features.sanitize_te`: Enables TE header sanitization\n- `envoy.reloadable_features.consistent_header_validation`: RFC-compliant header validation\n- `envoy.reloadable_features.sanitize_http2_headers_without_nghttp2`: Header validation without nghttp2\n- `envoy.uhv.allow_non_compliant_characters_in_path`: Compatibility mode for path characters\n\n### Architecture Summary\n\nThe header injection prevention is enforced at multiple levels:\n\n1. **Codec Level**: HTTP/1, HTTP/2, and HTTP/3 codecs validate headers during parsing\n2. **Connection Manager Level**: The connection manager sanitizes internal headers and applies transformations\n3. **Header Validator Extensions**: Pluggable header validators provide protocol-specific validation\n4. **Utility Functions**: Shared utility functions handle common validation patterns (hostname, method, scheme)\n5. **Header Map Level**: The base HeaderMap class validates header strings cannot contain control characters\n\nThis multi-layered approach ensures comprehensive protection against HTTP request header injection attacks across all supported HTTP protocols, with configurable behavior for different security and compatibility requirements."
