  "text": "## HTTP Request Header Injection Validation in Envoy v1.31.2\n\nEnvoy implements comprehensive HTTP request header injection validation and prevention through multiple layers of defense across three main HTTP protocol implementations (HTTP/1.1, HTTP/2, HTTP/3).\n\n### Core Header Validation Functions\n\n**Basic Header Validation (source/common/http/header_utility.cc)**\n- `validHeaderString()` (envoy/http/header_map.h): Validates header strings do not contain embedded NULLs, carriage returns (\\r), or line feeds (\\n)\n- `headerNameIsValid()`: Validates header names according to HTTP semantics, checks for valid characters, handles pseudo-headers starting with ':'\n- `headerValueIsValid()`: Validates header values using http2::adapter::HeaderValidator for RFC compliance\n- `checkValidRequestHeaders()`: Comprehensive validation of upstream request headers (guarded by \"envoy.reloadable_features.validate_upstream_headers\" runtime flag)\n- `checkRequiredRequestHeaders()`: Ensures required headers (:method, :path, :authority for CONNECT) are present\n- `requestHeadersValid()`: Validates authority, method, and scheme headers for compliance\n\n### Internal Header Stripping and Forbidden Headers\n\n**Edge Request Header Sanitization (source/common/http/conn_manager_utility.cc)**\n- `cleanInternalHeaders()`: Removes internal x-envoy-* headers from edge requests to prevent clients from injecting values that should only come from trusted internal sources. Headers stripped include:\n  - x-envoy-decorator-operation\n  - x-envoy-downstream-service-cluster  \n  - x-envoy-downstream-service-node\n  - x-envoy-original-path\n  - x-envoy-retry-on / x-envoy-retry-grpc-on\n  - x-envoy-max-retries\n  - x-envoy-upstream-alt-stat-name\n  - x-envoy-upstream-request-timeout-ms / x-envoy-upstream-request-per-try-timeout-ms\n  - x-envoy-force-trace\n  - x-envoy-ip-tags\n  - x-envoy-original-url\n  - x-envoy-hedge-on-per-try-timeout\n\n### Connection Header Sanitization\n\n**HTTP/1.1 Connection Header Handling (source/common/http/utility.cc)**\n- `sanitizeConnectionHeader()`: Prevents header injection via the Connection header by:\n  - Limiting nominated headers to 10 maximum (prevents DOS)\n  - Removing headers nominated by the Connection header\n  - Rejecting if Connection nominates x-forwarded-* headers or pseudo-headers (RFC violation)\n  - Sanitizing the TE (Transfer-Encoding) header when nominated\n  - Validating TE values do not exceed 256 bytes\n  - Validates nominated headers conform to HTTP hop-by-hop semantics\n\n### HTTP/1.1 Specific Validation\n\n**Header Codec Validation (source/common/http/http1/codec_impl.cc)**\n- Validates header values for invalid characters using `headerValueIsValid()`\n- Checks header names and values conform to HTTP/1.1 semantics\n- Validates path formatting and rejects invalid URLs\n- Calls `sanitizeConnectionHeader()` during request header processing\n- Detects invalid header values (non-ASCII, control characters)\n\n**HTTP/1 Header Validator (source/extensions/http/header_validators/envoy_default/http1_header_validator.cc)**\n- `sanitizeContentLength()`: Removes content-length from CONNECT requests or when transfer-encoding:chunked is present\n- `sanitizeHeadersWithUnderscores()`: Removes or rejects headers with underscores based on configuration\n- `sanitizePathWithFragment()`: Strips URL fragments from paths\n- `transformRequestHeaders()`: Applies all sanitization transformations in sequence\n- Validates header character sets conform to RFC specifications\n- Supports path normalization with escaped slash handling\n\n### HTTP/2 Specific Validation  \n\n**HTTP/2 Forbidden Headers (source/extensions/http/header_validators/envoy_default/http2_header_validator.cc)**\n- Enforces strict validation that connection-specific headers are forbidden in HTTP/2 per RFC 9113\n- Forbidden header list: transfer-encoding, connection, upgrade, keep-alive, proxy-connection\n- Returns ConnectionHeaderSanitization rejection